race.comment: BAKED (11) resumes. She's a lightly raced filly who has only managed two runs in two campaigns to date, well supported on each occasion. Her latest trial at Sandown Hillside was good and she profiles well for this from the pole draw. MISS NAVRATILOVA (12) has shown promise in three runs to date, perhaps just finding 1400m a touch too far last time at Wodonga. The two runs prior rate well for this. EARTHING (6) is a well bred colt by Snitzel out of dual Listed winner In Good Health who raced in the same colours. Watch the market for a lead. UNA GENTLE (13) was close up at Colac last time and has each way claims, as does CHAMPAGNE EXPRESS (10) who can roll forward and give a sight.
